title: Sweet house in a co-living community
posting_body: For rent: a 1000 sf, 2/1 home with hardwood floors, built in 1948.
It is part of a 5 household co-living community in central Austin.

The shared back yard is park-like, completely fenced, with an outdoor dining pavilion, a large fire ring, chicken coop and huge fenced vegetable/flower/herb garden from which residents are invited to harvest.
Rent is $2300, possibly less once new property tax percentages are out, with a $1000 deposit.
This is a home where you can put down deep roots and share in the work, support and camaraderie of a friendly community comprised of older individuals.
